WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:02.390 --> 00:00:03.625
- What does Tim wanna show us?

2
00:00:03.658 --> 00:00:05.590
- He'll kill me if I ruin the surprise.

3
00:00:05.625 --> 00:00:06.625
- It's not a waffle truck.

4
00:00:06.658 --> 00:00:08.724
I asked. - Oh.

5
00:00:08.757 --> 00:00:09.824
- Welcome.

6
00:00:09.857 --> 00:00:12.156
Wanted you guys be the first to see my new office.

7
00:00:12.190 --> 00:00:13.724
Look. if I'm gonna be a more "out on the street"

8
00:00:13.757 --> 00:00:15.624
watch commander. I need to take my office with me.

9
00:00:15.657 --> 00:00:18.356
- Is this the new interceptor utility vehicle?

10
00:00:18.389 --> 00:00:22.723
- It is. 700 horsepower. 8.000-pound towing capacity.

11
00:00:22.756 --> 00:00:25.623
Level 4 ballistic door panels. dark mode.

12
00:00:25.656 --> 00:00:28.622
and 270-degree monitoring to analyze moving objects

13
00:00:28.655 --> 00:00:29.855
for potential threat levels.

14
00:00:29.888 --> 00:00:31.487
- He calls it a Super Shop.

15
00:00:31.520 --> 00:00:33.187
- That's a working title.

16
00:00:33.220 --> 00:00:36.622
- You see. we got hats and bats. infrared camera.

17
00:00:36.655 --> 00:00:37.754
breaching tools.

18
00:00:37.787 --> 00:00:39.220
- Oh. yeah.

19
00:00:39.253 --> 00:00:41.453
- Two 32-inch screens. - Whoo.

20
00:00:41.486 --> 00:00:42.754
- Wow.

21
00:00:42.787 --> 00:00:44.152
Can I be watch commander?

22
00:00:44.186 --> 00:00:45.720
- No. but you are riding with me today.

23
00:00:45.753 --> 00:00:47.686
- Yes. - Oh. hey. show them Droney.

24
00:00:47.720 --> 00:00:49.753
- Oh. yeah. Check this out.

25
00:00:57.251 --> 00:00:58.317
Isn't he cute?

26
00:00:58.351 --> 00:01:00.184
- She. - Really?

27
00:01:00.217 --> 00:01:01.484
- Yeah. - Oh.

28
00:01:01.517 --> 00:01:02.484
- Super Shop makes the Batmobile look

29
00:01:02.517 --> 00:01:03.517
like a kiddie toy.

30
00:01:03.551 --> 00:01:06.217
And I can control it all right here from my phone.

31
00:01:08.618 --> 00:01:09.618
See?

32
00:01:11.651 --> 00:01:13.149
Damn it.

33
00:01:13.183 --> 00:01:15.750
Whoa. whoa. damn it.

34
00:01:15.783 --> 00:01:17.617
- Playing Tim's Pump Up Jams.

35
00:01:18.717 --> 00:01:21.882
Stop. stop. stop.

36
00:01:23.000 --> 00:01:29.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

37
00:01:30.247 --> 00:01:31.848
- It's not gonna be as easy as you think.

38
00:01:31.881 --> 00:01:34.480
- Based on this morning's demonstration. I'm well aware.

39
00:01:34.513 --> 00:01:36.280
- It's not just that you're taking

40
00:01:36.313 --> 00:01:37.848
the watch commander duties on patrol.

41
00:01:37.881 --> 00:01:41.747
You're also exposing yourself to chain-of-command confusion

42
00:01:41.780 --> 00:01:44.213
when you land at a scene. even if you stay in the SUV.

43
00:01:44.246 --> 00:01:45.847
- Super Shop.

44
00:01:45.880 --> 00:01:47.379
It's a working name.

45
00:01:52.779 --> 00:01:53.879
Good morning.

46
00:01:53.913 --> 00:01:55.445
- Good morning. - Good morning.

47
00:01:55.478 --> 00:01:56.879
- All right. listen up. we're gonna do things

48
00:01:56.913 --> 00:01:58.613
a little different today.

49
00:01:58.646 --> 00:02:00.878
There'll be two supervisors out on the street.

50
00:02:00.912 --> 00:02:03.612
Sergeant Chen and myself.

51
00:02:04.745 --> 00:02:06.444
I know. I know.

52
00:02:06.477 --> 00:02:08.277
No one wants the boss showing up to their calls.

53
00:02:08.310 --> 00:02:09.744
second-guessing their every move.

54
00:02:09.777 --> 00:02:12.744
That is not my intention. okay? Nothing has to change.

55
00:02:12.777 --> 00:02:14.309
I just put wheels on my office.

56
00:02:14.343 --> 00:02:15.309
And while we work out the details.

57
00:02:15.343 --> 00:02:17.677
Officer Nolan will be riding with me to help

58
00:02:17.711 --> 00:02:19.477
facilitate the transition.

59
00:02:19.510 --> 00:02:21.142
Any questions?

60
00:02:21.176 --> 00:02:22.509
- Can I pick the playlist?

61
00:02:23.876 --> 00:02:25.710
It's a dumb question.

62
00:02:25.743 --> 00:02:28.342
- All right. second order of business. Officer Juarez

63
00:02:28.375 --> 00:02:29.475
will be on temporary duty assignment

64
00:02:29.508 --> 00:02:31.407
with the Detectives Bureau.

65
00:02:31.441 --> 00:02:32.475
Did you choose your focus?

66
00:02:32.508 --> 00:02:34.475
- Yes. Missing Persons.

67
00:02:34.508 --> 00:02:36.207
- Oof.

68
00:02:36.240 --> 00:02:38.541
- Are you sure about that? - Yeah.

69
00:02:38.574 --> 00:02:40.306
- Your call.

70
00:02:40.340 --> 00:02:41.574
All right. I have some updates from the night shift.

71
00:02:41.608 --> 00:02:44.541
- Is Missing Persons really that bad?

72
00:02:44.574 --> 00:02:46.607
- Detective Desmond has a reputation.

73
00:02:46.640 --> 00:02:48.740
- Like a Harper reputation?

74
00:02:48.773 --> 00:02:51.873
- No. opposite.

75
00:02:51.907 --> 00:02:54.305
- Last day at the DA's office.

76
00:02:54.339 --> 00:02:55.606
Excited? - I'm relieved.

77
00:02:55.639 --> 00:02:57.472
When the DA had one foot in retirement.

78
00:02:57.505 --> 00:03:00.171
now that Vivian's DA-elect. she's gonna have free reign.

79
00:03:00.204 --> 00:03:01.539
- Well. none of that will matter

80
00:03:01.572 --> 00:03:03.338
once you quit and open a private practice in Malibu

81
00:03:03.371 --> 00:03:04.671
with a view of the ocean.

82
00:03:04.705 --> 00:03:07.403
- Uh. with that commute. you'd never see me again.

83
00:03:07.438 --> 00:03:10.605
- Well. in my dream. I also work in Malibu.

84
00:03:10.638 --> 00:03:12.170
I have a robot helicopter that flies

85
00:03:12.203 --> 00:03:14.203
the kids to school and a pony.

86
00:03:14.236 --> 00:03:15.470
- Well. sorry to kill another one of your dreams.

87
00:03:15.503 --> 00:03:17.336
But I already reached out to my old landlord.

88
00:03:17.369 --> 00:03:18.737
and the only view from that office

89
00:03:18.770 --> 00:03:20.804
is the Ethiopian place on the first floor.

90
00:03:20.837 --> 00:03:22.803
- Oh. before you go. make sure you pass off my cases

91
00:03:22.836 --> 00:03:24.336
to the right prosecutors.

92
00:03:24.369 --> 00:03:25.869
Daniels doesn't touch homicide.

93
00:03:25.903 --> 00:03:27.869
- Give mine to Cosgrove. He is solid.

94
00:03:27.903 --> 00:03:28.736
- That might be an issue.

95
00:03:28.769 --> 00:03:30.201
Cosgrove just quit.

96
00:03:30.234 --> 00:03:32.201
I gotta go. - Good luck.

97
00:03:32.234 --> 00:03:33.702
- Wesley. it's so good to see you.

98
00:03:33.735 --> 00:03:35.401
- Yeah. right.

99
00:03:35.435 --> 00:03:37.334
- I'm serious. No hard feelings on my end.

100
00:03:37.367 --> 00:03:38.334
- Yeah. because you destroyed me.

101
00:03:38.367 --> 00:03:39.668
- Well. exactly.

102
00:03:39.702 --> 00:03:41.200
I made good on the promise I made you when you

103
00:03:41.233 --> 00:03:42.601
threw your hat in the ring. It's nothing personal.

104
00:03:42.634 --> 00:03:45.167
In fact. I agree with you on a lot of the issues.

105
00:03:45.200 --> 00:03:47.199
And I know that together. we can take the DA's office

106
00:03:47.232 --> 00:03:48.434
in a positive direction.

107
00:03:48.467 --> 00:03:50.601
- Mm-hmm. - Mm-hmm.

108
00:03:50.634 --> 00:03:52.333
- You're not gonna fall for that. are you?

109
00:03:52.366 --> 00:03:53.733
- No.

110
00:03:53.766 --> 00:03:55.198
I was about to hand in my resignation letter.

111
00:03:55.231 --> 00:03:56.466
- Well. she won't accept it.

112
00:03:56.499 --> 00:03:58.265
With Cosgrove. Garcia. and Martin

113
00:03:58.298 --> 00:04:00.165
already out. she can't afford to lose anyone else.

114
00:04:00.198 --> 00:04:02.432
- Martin quit? - Keyed her car on the way out.

115
00:04:02.465 --> 00:04:04.565
- A hero to us all.

116
00:04:04.599 --> 00:04:06.331
- Come on.

117
00:04:07.765 --> 00:04:09.831
- Hey. sorry about the election.

118
00:04:09.864 --> 00:04:11.331
That should have been me facing Vivian.

119
00:04:11.365 --> 00:04:13.164
You were handed a poison chalice.

120
00:04:13.196 --> 00:04:14.831
- I drank from it willingly.

121
00:04:14.864 --> 00:04:16.330
How's Logan?

122
00:04:16.364 --> 00:04:17.730
- He's good.

123
00:04:17.763 --> 00:04:19.464
He just got another chip.

124
00:04:19.497 --> 00:04:22.196
He's been clean now almost four months.

125
00:04:22.228 --> 00:04:23.730
- That's great.

126
00:04:23.763 --> 00:04:25.396
What about you?

127
00:04:25.430 --> 00:04:26.597
You gonna do the Rothwell and Pierce thing?

128
00:04:26.630 --> 00:04:28.862
- No. I'm--

129
00:04:28.896 --> 00:04:30.195
I'm gonna stay here.

130
00:04:30.228 --> 00:04:31.562
And you should too.

131
00:04:31.596 --> 00:04:33.294
- Hmm.

132
00:04:33.329 --> 00:04:34.696
- Come on. Wes. you joined this place to change the culture

133
00:04:34.729 --> 00:04:38.261
from within. to ensure that justice.

134
00:04:38.294 --> 00:04:41.193
not punishment. was our paramount virtue. remember?

135
00:04:41.226 --> 00:04:43.260
- It's a very inspirational message

136
00:04:43.293 --> 00:04:45.428
that just lost by 23 points.

137
00:04:45.461 --> 00:04:47.193
Look. Vivian ran on tough on crime.

138
00:04:47.226 --> 00:04:48.694
She's gonna deliver.

139
00:04:48.727 --> 00:04:51.192
- Yeah. which is why the city needs people like us here

140
00:04:51.225 --> 00:04:52.660
now more than ever.

141
00:04:52.694 --> 00:04:54.694
Look. we still can make a difference.

142
00:04:54.726 --> 00:04:56.327
- Sean. - You're here already.

143
00:04:56.360 --> 00:04:58.192
Let's work together. one last time.

144
00:04:58.225 --> 00:05:00.191
If at the end of the day. you still wanna quit.

145
00:05:00.224 --> 00:05:02.191
I won't stay in your way.

146
00:05:02.224 --> 00:05:05.592
- This job is where ambition goes to die.

147
00:05:05.625 --> 00:05:06.592
- Wait. what?

148
00:05:06.625 --> 00:05:07.692
- Missing Persons.

149
00:05:07.725 --> 00:05:09.658
It's not a real department.

150
00:05:09.692 --> 00:05:12.725
It's a halfway house for cases on the way to real departments.

151
00:05:12.757 --> 00:05:15.425
- That's a lot of reports for a fake department.

152
00:05:15.457 --> 00:05:17.557
- 90% of these cases will solve themselves.

153
00:05:17.591 --> 00:05:19.591
Teenager just needed to blow off steam.

154
00:05:19.624 --> 00:05:22.457
A wife went on a bender. came home when she sobered up.

155
00:05:22.490 --> 00:05:24.324
Kid fell asleep playing hide-and-seek.

156
00:05:24.357 --> 00:05:25.823
- I've been on patrol for three years.

157
00:05:25.856 --> 00:05:28.456
I know most missing persons reports go nowhere.

158
00:05:28.489 --> 00:05:31.188
but there are people in this stack

159
00:05:31.221 --> 00:05:33.121
who are victims of real crimes.

160
00:05:33.155 --> 00:05:34.323
- Crimes with their own departments.

161
00:05:34.356 --> 00:05:36.855
like Trafficking or Homicide.

162
00:05:36.889 --> 00:05:38.288
- Sorry to interrupt.

163
00:05:38.322 --> 00:05:40.422
Homicide wants the McGrath case.

164
00:05:40.455 --> 00:05:42.187
Fisherman found the body.

165
00:05:42.220 --> 00:05:44.187
Looks like murder. - Rest in peace.

166
00:05:46.621 --> 00:05:49.421
- Okay. obviously. you know the job

167
00:05:49.454 --> 00:05:51.587
way better than I do. but wouldn't hurt

168
00:05:51.620 --> 00:05:53.287
to look through the case files.

169
00:05:53.321 --> 00:05:55.787
see if there's anyone we can help?

170
00:05:55.820 --> 00:05:56.753
- Knock yourself out.

171
00:06:03.285 --> 00:06:05.719
- This thing drives like a dream--

172
00:06:05.752 --> 00:06:07.719
and these seats.

173
00:06:07.752 --> 00:06:10.419
Ten minutes in a regular shop. my ass is barking.

174
00:06:10.452 --> 00:06:11.418
- Well. don't get used to it.

175
00:06:11.451 --> 00:06:13.451
You're just here while I work out the kinks.

176
00:06:13.484 --> 00:06:15.150
Once Penn is back from training.

177
00:06:15.183 --> 00:06:17.183
you're back in the shop. and I'm on my own.

178
00:06:17.217 --> 00:06:19.384
- I have a 4-15 at 5th and Western.

179
00:06:19.418 --> 00:06:22.517
RP reports two shirtless men circling each other.

180
00:06:22.550 --> 00:06:23.717
- 7-Adam-100 two blocks away.

181
00:06:23.750 --> 00:06:25.182
Show us responding.

182
00:06:25.216 --> 00:06:26.517
- Are you sure?

183
00:06:26.550 --> 00:06:28.716
Sounds like your basic alcohol-fueled slugfest.

184
00:06:28.749 --> 00:06:30.317
- Yeah. I have to test response times on even

185
00:06:30.349 --> 00:06:32.148
the most basic of calls.

186
00:06:34.181 --> 00:06:35.583
Captain's calling.

187
00:06:35.616 --> 00:06:36.682
Bradford.

188
00:06:36.715 --> 00:06:37.848
- Can you hold?

189
00:06:37.882 --> 00:06:39.682
- Yeah. I'll hold.

190
00:06:43.181 --> 00:06:46.515
I'll be right there. - I got this one.

191
00:06:46.548 --> 00:06:48.414
LAPD. You guys. break it up.

192
00:06:48.447 --> 00:06:49.847
Come on.

193
00:06:49.881 --> 00:06:51.280
- Sorry. he was called into a meeting.

194
00:06:51.314 --> 00:06:52.647
Can you hold just a minute longer?

195
00:06:52.681 --> 00:06:54.581
Thanks. - No. I'm out on--

196
00:06:58.313 --> 00:06:59.713
- Hey.

197
00:07:01.746 --> 00:07:02.713
- Hey. keep your hands where I can see them.

198
00:07:02.746 --> 00:07:05.179
Just stay right there.

199
00:07:05.212 --> 00:07:07.445
- Sorry to keep you waiting. - No problem. sir.

200
00:07:07.478 --> 00:07:08.679
We're getting a lot of complaints

201
00:07:08.712 --> 00:07:11.144
about vagrants in Stoner Park.

202
00:07:11.178 --> 00:07:13.678
- I've gotta say. renaming it would be a strong start.

203
00:07:13.711 --> 00:07:16.178
- It's important that people feel safe in public places.

204
00:07:16.211 --> 00:07:17.711
- Couldn't agree more.

205
00:07:17.744 --> 00:07:19.444
I'll have additional units in the area starting today.

206
00:07:19.477 --> 00:07:21.177
Okay. is that it?

207
00:07:21.210 --> 00:07:22.843
- One more thing. I just wanna say.

208
00:07:22.877 --> 00:07:24.311
your tireless commitment to justice

209
00:07:24.344 --> 00:07:25.843
and the people of this city--

210
00:07:25.877 --> 00:07:27.843
- Thank you. sir.

211
00:07:27.877 --> 00:07:30.310
- Hey. hey. hey. hey.

212
00:07:30.343 --> 00:07:31.510
Good job. sir.

213
00:07:31.543 --> 00:07:33.310
You supervised the hell out of that.

214
00:07:33.343 --> 00:07:35.108
- You're still here.

215
00:07:35.143 --> 00:07:36.709
- And I think I found a workable case.

216
00:07:36.742 --> 00:07:39.576
Sadie Bell. 30. was reported missing last week.

217
00:07:39.609 --> 00:07:41.309
but according to her best friend. Joe.

218
00:07:41.342 --> 00:07:43.441
Sadie never misses visitation with her kid

219
00:07:43.474 --> 00:07:46.508
on the first Tuesday of every month.

220
00:07:46.541 --> 00:07:49.174
- Walk with me.

221
00:07:49.207 --> 00:07:51.508
Reporting party's address?

222
00:07:51.540 --> 00:07:53.174
- 5200 6th Street.

223
00:07:53.207 --> 00:07:54.307
- It's a homeless shelter.

224
00:07:54.340 --> 00:07:56.373
Joe is unhoused. meaning Sadie's unhoused.

225
00:07:56.407 --> 00:07:57.840
Not the most reliable bunch.

226
00:07:57.873 --> 00:08:00.173
- On the other hand. sir. unhoused women

227
00:08:00.206 --> 00:08:02.839
are highly vulnerable to physical and sexual assaults.

228
00:08:02.873 --> 00:08:05.172
- True. and they're also more likely to be

229
00:08:05.205 --> 00:08:06.839
substance abusers who miss things like supervised

230
00:08:06.872 --> 00:08:08.439
child visitations.

231
00:08:08.472 --> 00:08:09.838
- Oh. I know.

232
00:08:09.872 --> 00:08:11.105
Well. I think it's worth investigating.

233
00:08:11.139 --> 00:08:12.838
So what's our first step?

234
00:08:12.872 --> 00:08:15.171
- Why are you so gung ho. Officer Juarez?

235
00:08:15.204 --> 00:08:17.737
And don't just say the indefatigability of youth.

236
00:08:20.604 --> 00:08:23.704
- My sister was abducted when I was a child. sir.

237
00:08:23.737 --> 00:08:28.437
I lived the fear of not knowing where a loved one is.

238
00:08:28.470 --> 00:08:31.269
- Understandable and quite noble.

239
00:08:31.303 --> 00:08:33.770
But I would caution you that the thousand files

240
00:08:33.803 --> 00:08:36.303
in my office are not an unending stack

241
00:08:36.336 --> 00:08:37.669
of potential happy endings.

242
00:08:37.702 --> 00:08:39.569
For the subset that are not just

243
00:08:39.602 --> 00:08:42.702
runaways or miscommunications.

244
00:08:42.735 --> 00:08:44.569
the endings are mostly heartbreaking.

245
00:08:48.601 --> 00:08:50.301
- I haven't had a chance to review the reports.

246
00:08:50.334 --> 00:08:51.834
but it's at the top of my list.

247
00:08:51.868 --> 00:08:53.701
Okay. I appreciate the reminder.

248
00:08:55.467 --> 00:08:57.433
How did Grey make it look so easy?

249
00:08:57.466 --> 00:08:58.800
- Well. the scowl helped.

250
00:08:58.833 --> 00:09:01.166
Yeah. you don't wanna bother that face

251
00:09:01.199 --> 00:09:03.166
with anything less than an absolute emergency.

252
00:09:03.199 --> 00:09:05.166
- My scowl is legendary.

253
00:09:05.199 --> 00:09:06.532
- It was.

254
00:09:06.566 --> 00:09:07.799
But then Lucy moved in.

255
00:09:09.332 --> 00:09:10.699
You know what?

256
00:09:10.732 --> 00:09:12.699
I take it back.

257
00:09:12.731 --> 00:09:14.831
Hey. Dash. everything all right?

258
00:09:14.865 --> 00:09:16.698
- Hey. so lesson for the future.

259
00:09:16.731 --> 00:09:19.464
if somebody asks if you wanna see a dead body. say no.

260
00:09:20.864 --> 00:09:23.231
- Dash. are you standing over a dead body?

261
00:09:25.197 --> 00:09:25.697
- Yep.

262
00:09:28.263 --> 00:09:29.297
- He's been here for at least a day.

263
00:09:29.330 --> 00:09:30.430
Won't know how long for sure until TID gets here

264
00:09:30.463 --> 00:09:32.497
and we turn him over.

265
00:09:32.530 --> 00:09:33.563
- Kenneth Morris.

266
00:09:33.596 --> 00:09:35.796
- K-Dog? For real?

267
00:09:35.829 --> 00:09:37.829
Oh. Kenny's my English teacher.

268
00:09:37.863 --> 00:09:39.663
Was my English teacher.

269
00:09:39.696 --> 00:09:42.129
- Okay. so who found the body?

270
00:09:42.162 --> 00:09:43.262
- Dakota.

271
00:09:43.296 --> 00:09:45.162
We're in fourth period together.

272
00:09:45.195 --> 00:09:46.261
But I didn't think it was real.

273
00:09:46.295 --> 00:09:48.361
She's always gossiping about something.

274
00:09:48.395 --> 00:09:50.528
Last week. she told me she was quitting school

275
00:09:50.562 --> 00:09:51.694
