335
00:11:47.248 --> 00:11:49.382
- Oh. no thank you.

336
00:11:49.415 --> 00:11:52.215
I was legally emancipated when I was 13

337
00:11:52.248 --> 00:11:55.514
so I could work adult hours on set.

338
00:11:55.548 --> 00:11:56.748
I don't need them here.

339
00:11:56.781 --> 00:12:00.414
- Great. Let's interview you first.

340
00:12:00.447 --> 00:12:02.547
- Please tell me Jack won't be going there.

341
00:12:02.580 --> 00:12:05.413
- It's not definite. but Jack's preschool

342
00:12:05.446 --> 00:12:08.346
is the feeder school for Coastwood.

343
00:12:08.380 --> 00:12:09.812
It would be an easy transition.

344
00:12:09.847 --> 00:12:13.146
- Logistically. maybe. but emotionally. won't you--

345
00:12:13.178 --> 00:12:15.279
- Die a little? Yes.

346
00:12:15.312 --> 00:12:18.112
But LA elementary schools are more competitive than Stanford.

347
00:12:18.145 --> 00:12:19.812
and having an easy path would save

348
00:12:19.846 --> 00:12:21.645
hundreds of hours of stress.

349
00:12:21.678 --> 00:12:24.511
- Yeah. but then he'd be going to school with kids like these.

350
00:12:24.545 --> 00:12:26.077
- That's where it falls apart.

351
00:12:26.111 --> 00:12:28.411
- And what can you tell me about Morris?

352
00:12:28.444 --> 00:12:29.677
- Oh. Kenny was such a sweetie.

353
00:12:29.710 --> 00:12:31.811
Even when I had to miss a lot of class last year.

354
00:12:31.845 --> 00:12:33.377
he was so chill about it.

355
00:12:33.410 --> 00:12:34.410
- Why did you have to miss school?

356
00:12:34.443 --> 00:12:36.243
- I was doing this indie project.

357
00:12:36.277 --> 00:12:38.243
We were supposed to premiere at Sundance.

358
00:12:38.277 --> 00:12:40.276
but then the director had all these. like.

359
00:12:40.309 --> 00:12:42.376
"harassment allegations" or whatever

360
00:12:42.409 --> 00:12:43.676
and got basically blackballed.

361
00:12:43.709 --> 00:12:46.476
And now my career has to suffer.

362
00:12:46.509 --> 00:12:48.142
- Did Kenneth have any disagreements

363
00:12:48.175 --> 00:12:49.809
with other teachers. faculty?

364
00:12:49.843 --> 00:12:53.408
- No. I really can't imagine anyone wanting to hurt Ken-Ken.

365
00:12:53.441 --> 00:12:55.141
He wasn't traditionally attractive. sure.

366
00:12:55.174 --> 00:12:57.808
but that's no reason to be murdered. right?

367
00:13:00.140 --> 00:13:01.240
- Can I vape in here?

368
00:13:01.274 --> 00:13:02.541
I have a note from my therapist.

369
00:13:02.574 --> 00:13:04.807
- He does. I have it right here.

370
00:13:04.841 --> 00:13:06.473
- No.

371
00:13:06.506 --> 00:13:08.673
Who first told you about the body in the woods?

372
00:13:08.706 --> 00:13:11.774
- It was Sushi Tuesday. so I was pretty laser-focused

373
00:13:11.807 --> 00:13:15.273
on whether I wanted ahi or uni.

374
00:13:15.306 --> 00:13:16.806
I think I ended up getting both.

375
00:13:16.840 --> 00:13:19.205
- Let's focus here.

376
00:13:19.238 --> 00:13:21.205
Where did you hear about the body?

377
00:13:21.238 --> 00:13:23.772
- Well. I remember Autumn mentioning something earlier

378
00:13:23.805 --> 00:13:26.404
in the day when she was talking to Ilya.

379
00:13:26.437 --> 00:13:28.137
but Ilya said he had heard it from--

380
00:13:28.170 --> 00:13:29.772
- Zoey.

381
00:13:29.805 --> 00:13:31.538
I guess she originally saw something about it in a DM

382
00:13:31.571 --> 00:13:34.137
from Linette when she was going through CJ's phone.

383
00:13:34.170 --> 00:13:36.537
And given what happened on the school trip last year.

384
00:13:36.570 --> 00:13:40.803
it is super sketchy that he was DM'ing Linette.

385
00:13:40.837 --> 00:13:42.136
- Back up.

386
00:13:42.169 --> 00:13:43.770
Where do we think the rumor started?

387
00:13:43.803 --> 00:13:45.335
- Nowhere. everywhere.

388
00:13:45.369 --> 00:13:46.536
- How are we further from figuring

389
00:13:46.569 --> 00:13:48.202
this out than when we started?

390
00:13:48.235 --> 00:13:49.802
- I called for backup.

391
00:13:49.836 --> 00:13:50.802
- Hi again.

392
00:13:50.836 --> 00:13:52.802
- Thank God. normal teenager.

393
00:13:52.836 --> 00:13:56.668
No offense. it's just your classmates tend to be--

394
00:13:56.702 --> 00:13:58.334
- Overwhelmed by their own champagne problems.

395
00:13:58.368 --> 00:13:59.801
I get it.

396
00:13:59.835 --> 00:14:01.667
My dysfunction is a little bit more proletariat.

397
00:14:01.701 --> 00:14:03.234
- Guess that's one way to put it.

398
00:14:03.267 --> 00:14:04.200
- Yeah. I don't really hang out with them

399
00:14:04.233 --> 00:14:06.100
much outside of school.

400
00:14:06.133 --> 00:14:07.767
And that's not just because I didn't make "Forbes"

401
00:14:07.800 --> 00:14:10.400
20 under 20. but it's definitely a factor.

402
00:14:10.433 --> 00:14:11.800
- Well. we're not done with the interviews yet.

403
00:14:11.834 --> 00:14:13.533
but so far. no one we have talked to

404
00:14:13.566 --> 00:14:15.633
has said they're the one who started the rumor.

405
00:14:15.666 --> 00:14:17.332
They all claim to have heard it from someone else.

406
00:14:17.366 --> 00:14:18.366
- Right.

407
00:14:18.399 --> 00:14:20.266
So Reese heard about it from CJ.

408
00:14:20.299 --> 00:14:24.098
who heard about it from Zoey. who saw it in a DM from--

409
00:14:24.131 --> 00:14:26.131
- You said that Reese heard about it from CJ?

410
00:14:26.164 --> 00:14:27.398
- That's what she told us.

411
00:14:27.431 --> 00:14:28.465
- That doesn't make any sense.

412
00:14:28.498 --> 00:14:30.531
They got in a huge fight last week about. you know.

413
00:14:30.564 --> 00:14:32.130
whether or not sending nudes to other people

414
00:14:32.163 --> 00:14:33.631
counts as cheating.

415
00:14:33.665 --> 00:14:35.130
They haven't spoken to each other since.

416
00:14:35.163 --> 00:14:36.130
And word in the halls is that Zoey

417
00:14:36.163 --> 00:14:37.664
and CJ are the new it couple.

418
00:14:37.697 --> 00:14:38.797
- Oh. my God. yes. I was

419
00:14:38.831 --> 00:14:40.396
totally picking up on that vibe.

420
00:14:40.429 --> 00:14:43.062
But I saw that Zoey wasn't following CJ on Instagram.

421
00:14:43.096 --> 00:14:44.664
so I put it from my head.

422
00:14:44.697 --> 00:14:46.396
But when I doubled back to check.

423
00:14:46.429 --> 00:14:48.796
it looks like she does follow him. but only with her finsta.

424
00:14:48.830 --> 00:14:51.228
- With her finsta. yeah.

425
00:14:51.262 --> 00:14:52.763
- Okay. this is-- this is actually

426
00:14:52.796 --> 00:14:53.795
all starting to make sense.

427
00:14:53.829 --> 00:14:55.529
- It is?

428
00:14:55.562 --> 00:14:57.662
- So Linette and Emma. they went to the bathroom

429
00:14:57.695 --> 00:15:01.127
to do a fit check for their joint Instagram account.

430
00:15:01.160 --> 00:15:02.762
And Linette said that she hears somebody

431
00:15:02.794 --> 00:15:04.528
crying in one of the stalls.

432
00:15:04.561 --> 00:15:06.327
And she says that it's Reese because

433
00:15:06.361 --> 00:15:08.661
she recognizes her leather Tabis.

434
00:15:08.694 --> 00:15:11.661
Travis tells Paul in the parking lot that he heard about

435
00:15:11.694 --> 00:15:15.260
a dead body from "some bitch in first period."

436
00:15:15.293 --> 00:15:17.526
and who does he have first period with?

437
00:15:17.559 --> 00:15:19.125
Reese.

438
00:15:19.158 --> 00:15:21.259
And Dash heard about the body from Dakota.

439
00:15:21.292 --> 00:15:22.659
who is Reese's second-best friend.

440
00:15:22.692 --> 00:15:26.258
but she has been fighting for that number one spot.

441
00:15:26.291 --> 00:15:29.391
So. I mean. she would do anything that Reese says.

442
00:15:29.424 --> 00:15:32.224
- So if Reese told Dakota to lie about where

443
00:15:32.258 --> 00:15:33.524
she heard about the body--

444
00:15:33.557 --> 00:15:35.390
- This is all coming back to Reese.

445
00:15:35.423 --> 00:15:38.658
- Okay. so is Reese witness zero?

446
00:15:38.691 --> 00:15:39.758
Or is she the killer?

447
00:15:41.423 --> 00:15:42.690
- Sadie?

448
00:15:49.289 --> 00:15:53.522
Yeah. okay.

449
00:15:53.555 --> 00:15:56.756
You know. the night Sadie went missing. it was pouring rain.

450
00:15:56.789 --> 00:15:58.255
and the shelter was full.

451
00:15:58.288 --> 00:16:00.788
So I'm thinking she crawled in here to stay dry

452
00:16:00.822 --> 00:16:02.788
and got trapped.

453
00:16:02.822 --> 00:16:05.187
- Couple months ago. I found a bunch of guys

454
00:16:05.220 --> 00:16:07.087
living it up in an access tunnel--

455
00:16:07.120 --> 00:16:10.754
electricity. Wi-Fi. the whole thing.

456
00:16:10.787 --> 00:16:12.654
They had the right idea.

457
00:16:12.687 --> 00:16:14.453
- But you also have electricity and Wi-Fi.

458
00:16:14.486 --> 00:16:18.520
- Yeah. but I have to pay for it.

459
00:16:18.554 --> 00:16:20.653
- You know. one of those gates. if they locked behind her.

460
00:16:20.686 --> 00:16:23.452
she could be trapped or too injured to crawl out.

461
00:16:23.485 --> 00:16:24.786
- Yeah. but at this point. she's probably

462
00:16:24.820 --> 00:16:26.785
dead from dehydration.

463
00:16:26.819 --> 00:16:28.151
Wait. what?

464
00:16:31.251 --> 00:16:35.784
- Sadie. if you can hear me. make a sound.

465
00:16:46.149 --> 00:16:47.783
Desmond. - Where are you?

466
00:16:47.817 --> 00:16:49.783
- I'm inside a service tunnel looking for Sadie.

467
00:16:49.817 --> 00:16:52.115
- I called the shelter. She showed up this morning.

468
00:16:52.148 --> 00:16:53.782
- You're kidding. Well. why didn't they call us?

469
00:16:53.816 --> 00:16:55.115
- They never do.

470
00:16:55.148 --> 00:16:56.649
- So she was fine this whole time?

471
00:16:56.682 --> 00:16:58.215
- Yeah. it turns out that her friend

472
00:16:58.249 --> 00:16:59.516
had the visitation day wrong.

473
00:16:59.549 --> 00:17:01.516
But hey. cheer up.

474
00:17:01.549 --> 00:17:03.516
At least you only wasted your own time.

475
00:17:07.380 --> 00:17:09.648
- I am so sorry.

476
00:17:17.680 --> 00:17:21.112
- Oh. hey. Celina.

477
00:17:21.145 --> 00:17:23.779
Hey. I heard about the missing person who wasn't missing.

478
00:17:23.813 --> 00:17:25.613
- Already? I just got back.

479
00:17:25.646 --> 00:17:26.779
- Smitty was with you.

480
00:17:26.813 --> 00:17:28.646
- Right.

481
00:17:28.679 --> 00:17:30.311
Oh. I'm gonna owe a lot of favors

482
00:17:30.345 --> 00:17:32.645
after dragging the cavalry through the sewers.

483
00:17:32.678 --> 00:17:34.178
- Okay. first of all. do not refer

484
00:17:34.211 --> 00:17:36.512
to any group that includes Smitty as the cavalry.

485
00:17:36.545 --> 00:17:38.210
And second. those guys will forgive you.

486
00:17:38.244 --> 00:17:39.645
Or you know. somebody else will screw up way worse.

487
00:17:39.678 --> 00:17:41.478
and then they'll be focused on that.

488
00:17:41.512 --> 00:17:42.644
Whoa. I'm kidding.

489
00:17:42.677 --> 00:17:45.511
Hey. one misstep does not change the fact

490
00:17:45.544 --> 00:17:48.777
that your instincts here are legendary.

491
00:17:48.810 --> 00:17:50.511
So just take a second to wallow in this.

492
00:17:50.544 --> 00:17:52.243
but then get cleaned up and get back out there. yeah?

493
00:17:52.276 --> 00:17:53.375
- Yeah.

494
00:18:00.408 --> 00:18:01.775
- Oh. you're too kind.

495
00:18:01.809 --> 00:18:03.642
Yes. I'm really looking forward to working

496
00:18:03.675 --> 00:18:04.775
with you as well. Madam Mayor.

497
00:18:04.809 --> 00:18:06.742
Okay. bye.

498
00:18:06.775 --> 00:18:08.774
Sorry. I've been so busy.

499
00:18:08.808 --> 00:18:10.741
Before I make the big move upstairs.

500
00:18:10.774 --> 00:18:12.741
I wanted to get our house in order.

501
00:18:12.774 --> 00:18:13.841
a little bit clear the deck.

502
00:18:13.875 --> 00:18:18.740
So we have 27 felony arrests awaiting prosecution.

503
00:18:18.773 --> 00:18:20.740
We just do not have the manpower

504
00:18:20.773 --> 00:18:22.773
to take them all to trial. - Why?

505
00:18:22.807 --> 00:18:25.507
Did you lose some ADAs or something?

506
00:18:25.540 --> 00:18:28.105
- There's been turnover. yes.

507
00:18:28.138 --> 00:18:30.639
So I've got plea deals approved for all these cases.

508
00:18:30.672 --> 00:18:33.037
and I need you both to get them signed ASAP.

509
00:18:33.071 --> 00:18:34.606
- Murder 2?

510
00:18:34.639 --> 00:18:35.439
This guy robbed a convenience store.

511
00:18:35.472 --> 00:18:36.271
and the clerk had a heart attack.

512
00:18:36.304 --> 00:18:39.605
That is felony manslaughter at best.

513
00:18:39.638 --> 00:18:40.771
- The teen who pegged his principal with a football

514
00:18:40.805 --> 00:18:42.605
is assault with a deadly weapon?

515
00:18:42.638 --> 00:18:44.337
Did the DA sign off on these?

516
00:18:44.370 --> 00:18:46.103
- I pointed to the significant mandate

517
00:18:46.136 --> 00:18:47.770
voters handed me. and he agreed.

518
00:18:47.804 --> 00:18:50.103
- Well. their lawyers are not going to agree to these terms.

519
00:18:50.136 --> 00:18:51.236
- No.

520
00:18:51.269 --> 00:18:52.537
- Make them agree.

521
00:19:03.536 --> 00:19:05.602
- Apple Pruitt. She lives in my building.

522
00:19:05.635 --> 00:19:07.368
Her mother reported her missing a month ago

523
00:19:07.401 --> 00:19:09.768
when she didn't return from Coachella.

524
00:19:09.802 --> 00:19:12.702
- Every year. we get a spike in reports after Chella.

525
00:19:12.734 --> 00:19:15.234
This one time. this guy disassociated so hard

526
00:19:15.267 --> 00:19:16.501
he reported himself missing.

527
00:19:16.534 --> 00:19:18.367
- No. but this one's weird.

528
00:19:18.400 --> 00:19:20.634
Apple has a strong social media presence

529
00:19:20.667 --> 00:19:23.233
but didn't post anything about what happened this year.

530
00:19:23.266 --> 00:19:25.366
There was a massive dust storm.

531
00:19:25.399 --> 00:19:27.333
They canceled day two at the Sahara Tent.

532
00:19:27.366 --> 00:19:28.766
I mean. everyone was posting about it.

533
00:19:28.800 --> 00:19:31.031
- It's not exactly a smoking gun.

534
00:19:31.065 --> 00:19:32.699
- Okay. listen. I know how this sounds.

535
00:19:32.732 --> 00:19:34.265
but something is telling me to investigate.

536
00:19:36.131 --> 00:19:37.599
- I see what's going on.

537
00:19:37.632 --> 00:19:38.765
You said she lives in your building?

538
00:19:38.799 --> 00:19:41.499
- Mm-hmm. - Classic move.

539
00:19:41.532 --> 00:19:43.231
You take the case near your house

540
00:19:43.264 --> 00:19:45.364
so you can investigate it from your living room.

541
00:19:45.397 --> 00:19:46.364
When the shift ends. you're just

542
00:19:46.397 --> 00:19:48.196
a few steps from your futon.

543
00:19:48.230 --> 00:19:51.096
- I'm not trying to go home early.

544
00:19:51.129 --> 00:19:52.497
- That's too bad.

545
00:19:52.530 --> 00:19:54.497
I thought you were finally catching on.

546
00:19:57.095 --> 00:19:59.696
- There's no obvious connection between Reese and Mr. Morris.

547
00:19:59.729 --> 00:20:01.429
He did tutor her every week.

548
00:20:01.462 --> 00:20:03.228
but he tutored a lot of the kids.

549
00:20:03.261 --> 00:20:04.596
- Yeah. and his Venmo transactions

550
