didn't wanna be the one to call.

582
00:21:23.119 --> 00:21:27.220
- It didn't seem right that he was just lying out there.

583
00:21:27.253 --> 00:21:29.185
- How did you know he'd been killed?

584
00:21:32.253 --> 00:21:34.352
- I stayed late on Tuesday.

585
00:21:34.385 --> 00:21:36.486
My mom wanted to talk to Mr. Morris.

586
00:21:36.519 --> 00:21:39.486
She was so angry about Yale.

587
00:21:39.519 --> 00:21:41.084
She was yelling at him.

588
00:21:41.117 --> 00:21:42.618
and he wanted to talk somewhere private.

589
00:21:42.651 --> 00:21:46.351
so they went out back behind the school.

590
00:21:46.384 --> 00:21:49.184
I waited and waited.

591
00:21:49.218 --> 00:21:53.050
and finally. my mom came back.

592
00:21:53.083 --> 00:21:56.617
Just her. not him.

593
00:21:56.650 --> 00:22:00.317
and her hands were--

594
00:22:00.350 --> 00:22:03.082
she wouldn't talk about it. but I--

595
00:22:03.115 --> 00:22:06.749
I knew she did something.

596
00:22:06.783 --> 00:22:08.583
I didn't want any of this to happen.

597
00:22:08.616 --> 00:22:10.748
I don't even care about college.

598
00:22:17.113 --> 00:22:19.481
- Well. at least I know why I was failing the class.

599
00:22:19.514 --> 00:22:21.280
- Your mom wasn't bribing the teacher.

600
00:22:21.314 --> 00:22:23.047
- Yeah. and I never did any homework.

601
00:22:24.581 --> 00:22:26.214
- Listen. your mom is stuck at school.

602
00:22:26.247 --> 00:22:28.347
Things are about as hectic over there as you can imagine.

603
00:22:28.380 --> 00:22:30.480
So your dad's gonna come take you home.

604
00:22:30.513 --> 00:22:32.079
- Is that all right?

605
00:22:32.111 --> 00:22:33.613
- Yeah. it's fine.

606
00:22:33.646 --> 00:22:35.480
He shows up every six to eight months

607
00:22:35.513 --> 00:22:38.146
to remind everybody why my mom got sole custody.

608
00:22:38.179 --> 00:22:39.712
- I'm telling you. you cannot lose.

609
00:22:39.745 --> 00:22:41.745
You would be a fool not to invest.

610
00:22:41.779 --> 00:22:43.145
Hit me up on socials.

611
00:22:43.178 --> 00:22:44.479
I will tell you more about it. okay?

612
00:22:44.512 --> 00:22:46.744
Hey. there's my guy.

613
00:22:46.778 --> 00:22:48.312
How you doing?

614
00:22:48.344 --> 00:22:49.344
Still haven't had that growth spurt yet. huh?

615
00:22:49.377 --> 00:22:50.578
- I'm pacing myself.

616
00:22:50.611 --> 00:22:51.611
- Hey. sorry I haven't been around much.

617
00:22:51.644 --> 00:22:54.076
Been working crazy hours.

618
00:22:54.110 --> 00:22:57.344
But good news. Tiger Bear has one more investor signed on

619
00:22:57.376 --> 00:22:58.710
with a non-binding verbal agreement.

620
00:22:58.743 --> 00:23:00.543
- Tiger Bear? - It's a soup.

621
00:23:00.577 --> 00:23:02.343
It's a breakfast soup.

622
00:23:02.376 --> 00:23:04.075
- Dash. come on. no. that was the last one.

623
00:23:04.109 --> 00:23:06.409
Tiger Bear Whiskey Tequila's the whisquila start-up.

624
00:23:06.442 --> 00:23:08.342
It's gonna be huge.

625
00:23:08.375 --> 00:23:09.576
You should get in on the ground floor. champ.

626
00:23:09.609 --> 00:23:11.709
I'm telling you. an investment of 10 grand

627
00:23:11.742 --> 00:23:14.041
will triple by the end of the year guaranteed.

628
00:23:14.074 --> 00:23:15.475
- You do know your son found one of his teachers

629
00:23:15.508 --> 00:23:17.208
dead behind the school gym today.

630
00:23:17.241 --> 00:23:18.508
- Damn it.

631
00:23:20.374 --> 00:23:23.208
Sorry. sorry. okay. keep going.

632
00:23:23.241 --> 00:23:25.074
So Dash was working out. and--

633
00:23:25.107 --> 00:23:26.740
- Just take me home.

634
00:23:26.774 --> 00:23:28.207
Will I have to excavate the passenger seat

635
00:23:28.240 --> 00:23:30.173
for parking tickets again. or?

636
00:23:30.207 --> 00:23:32.140
- He's joking. I am a model citizen.

637
00:23:32.173 --> 00:23:33.506
Don't say that.

638
00:23:34.773 --> 00:23:36.172
- Dash.

639
00:23:37.473 --> 00:23:39.339
I'm around if you need me.

640
00:23:39.372 --> 00:23:41.072
- Listen. we gotta stop by my place first.

641
00:23:41.105 --> 00:23:42.206
But we'll make it a bro out.

642
00:23:42.239 --> 00:23:43.339
You know. we'll order some 'za.

643
00:23:43.371 --> 00:23:44.738
We'll watch last week's UFC.

644
00:23:44.772 --> 00:23:47.037
- Have a problem?

645
00:23:47.071 --> 00:23:48.705
- Just the universal unfairness of the world.

646
00:23:48.738 --> 00:23:50.371
nothing actionable.

647
00:23:53.337 --> 00:23:54.471
- Thanks for coming in.

648
00:23:54.504 --> 00:23:56.137
This is a plea deal.

649
00:23:56.170 --> 00:23:57.204
And before you ask. it's the best deal

650
00:23:57.237 --> 00:23:58.537
your client's gonna get.

651
00:23:58.571 --> 00:24:00.703
I know. murder 2. it seems excessive.

652
00:24:00.736 --> 00:24:03.070
I mean. all you did was rob a convenience store.

653
00:24:03.103 --> 00:24:06.703
It wasn't your fault that the clerk had a heart attack.

654
00:24:06.736 --> 00:24:08.436
The man had end-stage heart disease.

655
00:24:08.470 --> 00:24:12.203
Now. a jury could see that as extenuating circumstances.

656
00:24:12.236 --> 00:24:14.202
- I mean. if the jury was blind.

657
00:24:14.235 --> 00:24:16.469
maybe they'd see that as a gang tattoo.

658
00:24:16.502 --> 00:24:18.302
But I don't have to risk that possibility

659
