663
00:24:24.768 --> 00:24:26.733
been charged with perjury and false accusations

664
00:24:26.767 --> 00:24:28.434
in two other cases?

665
00:24:28.468 --> 00:24:30.467
- I mean. if you think you could do better at trial.

666
00:24:30.500 --> 00:24:33.133
you just push that plea deal right back at me.

667
00:24:54.764 --> 00:24:58.297
- The music is nowhere near too loud.

668
00:24:58.330 --> 00:24:59.697
- I'm Officer Juarez with LAPD.

669
00:24:59.730 --> 00:25:02.430
Yeah. I'm following your roommate. Apple Pruitt's case.

670
00:25:02.464 --> 00:25:04.063
Yeah. she hasn't come home. right?

671
00:25:04.096 --> 00:25:05.297
- No. no.

672
00:25:05.330 --> 00:25:08.329
I'm worried sick.

673
00:25:08.362 --> 00:25:10.296
- Do you mind if I come inside?

674
00:25:10.329 --> 00:25:12.463
- Sure. yeah. of course.

675
00:25:16.361 --> 00:25:19.061
I've actually been boxing up Apple's things all day.

676
00:25:19.094 --> 00:25:21.562
It's officially 30 days tomorrow.

677
00:25:21.595 --> 00:25:22.994
I just--I need someone else in here

678
00:25:23.028 --> 00:25:25.461
to help me with this crazy rent.

679
00:25:25.494 --> 00:25:28.194
not that Apple is great about paying.

680
00:25:28.227 --> 00:25:33.327
She doesn't believe in money or monogamy or cleaning.

681
00:25:33.360 --> 00:25:34.726
- She sounds like a lot.

682
00:25:34.760 --> 00:25:37.526
- Oh. don't get me wrong. she was--

683
00:25:37.560 --> 00:25:40.560
is one of my favorite people.

684
00:25:40.593 --> 00:25:42.692
just not the greatest at cohabitation.

685
00:25:42.725 --> 00:25:44.325
- Right.

686
00:25:44.358 --> 00:25:46.459
And the last time you saw her was

687
00:25:46.492 --> 00:25:48.192
right before she left for Coachella?

688
00:25:48.225 --> 00:25:51.459
- She loved going. even though she had her issues before.

689
00:25:51.491 --> 00:25:54.191
I mean. bad drugs and aggressive guys.

690
00:25:54.224 --> 00:25:57.124
she definitely had some scares.

691
00:25:57.157 --> 00:25:58.723
- And you think that's what happened to her?

692
00:25:58.757 --> 00:26:00.458
- I don't know.

693
00:26:00.491 --> 00:26:04.723
Um. I mean. I'm just trying to be helpful.

694
00:26:04.757 --> 00:26:07.722
But I'm desperate for you to find her.

695
00:26:07.756 --> 00:26:09.722
- Do you mind if I take a look at her bedroom?

696
00:26:09.756 --> 00:26:11.323
- Yeah. no problem.

697
00:26:11.355 --> 00:26:12.422
It's--it's right over there.

698
00:27:05.083 --> 00:27:06.050
- Augh!

699
00:27:06.083 --> 00:27:07.150
- I'm sorry!

700
00:27:07.184 --> 00:27:09.017
I'm sorry!

701
00:27:09.050 --> 00:27:10.183
It's not what you think!

702
00:27:24.215 --> 00:27:26.281
- Okay. okay.

703
00:27:57.044 --> 00:27:59.445
- This is Officer Juarez. badge number 53397.

704
00:27:59.478 --> 00:28:02.310
I'm code 4 with a possible 245 suspect.

705
00:28:02.343 --> 00:28:05.177
Also suspected of a 187. Send backup.

706
00:28:05.210 --> 00:28:08.676
I need an RA TID to my location.

707
00:28:10.210 --> 00:28:12.177
- You don't understand.

708
00:28:12.210 --> 00:28:16.276
She was the worst roommate ever.

709
00:28:16.309 --> 00:28:22.175
- Yeah. I'm pretty sure you're the worst roommate ever.

710
00:28:22.208 --> 00:28:25.141
- So this is just temporary.

711
00:28:25.175 --> 00:28:29.175
But the money train is chugging into the station.

712
00:28:29.208 --> 00:28:30.541
Then I'm gonna be playing the how many square feet

713
00:28:30.574 --> 00:28:33.374
is too many square feet game.

714
00:28:33.407 --> 00:28:35.174
You want some? - Uh. no. thanks.

715
00:28:35.207 --> 00:28:36.274
I just shotgunned some gasoline.

716
00:28:36.307 --> 00:28:38.007
- Ah.

717
00:28:44.039 --> 00:28:47.006
Oh. God.

718
00:28:47.039 --> 00:28:48.439
That's some serious stuff.

719
00:28:48.472 --> 00:28:51.439
Hey. so this fancy private school of yours--

720
00:28:51.472 --> 00:28:53.038
- Where a teacher was just murdered?

721
00:28:53.071 --> 00:28:54.439
- Really?

722
00:28:54.472 --> 00:28:56.571
- How have you not been paying attention?

723
00:28:56.604 --> 00:28:58.304
Never mind. of course you haven't.

724
00:28:58.337 --> 00:29:00.304
- All I'm saying is. you're in the perfect spot

725
00:29:00.337 --> 00:29:03.571
to help your dear old dad raise some cash money capital.

726
00:29:03.604 --> 00:29:05.970
I'm having supply issues in the Czech Republic.

727
00:29:06.004 --> 00:29:07.537
- Where they specialize in neither whiskey nor tequila.

728
00:29:07.570 --> 00:29:09.570
- Okay. That is besides the point.

729
00:29:09.603 --> 00:29:12.103
Anyways. you would be helping out the family

730
00:29:12.136 --> 00:29:13.703
if I can get you to make a few introductions.

731
00:29:13.737 --> 00:29:16.302
- If I say I'll think about it. will you take me home?

732
00:29:16.335 --> 00:29:19.035
- Come on. What's the rush? Party's just getting started.

733
00:29:20.469 --> 00:29:22.702
- Gus. I know you're in there.

734
00:29:22.736 --> 00:29:25.169
Open the damn door.

735
00:29:27.468 --> 00:29:28.967
We're gonna go out the window.

736
00:29:29.001 --> 00:29:30.435
No. we're not.

737
00:29:30.468 --> 00:29:32.168
- I can hear you in there.

738
00:29:32.201 --> 00:29:33.567
Open the door. or we kick it in.

739
00:29:33.600 --> 00:29:38.267
- Uh. okay. so a few of my friends are here.

740
00:29:38.300 --> 00:29:39.567
You gotta go hide.

741
00:29:39.600 --> 00:29:41.100
- Why would I hide from your friends?

742
00:29:41.133 --> 00:29:42.434
- Just go.

743
00:29:42.466 --> 00:29:45.033
And don't come out no matter what.

744
00:29:51.466 --> 00:29:53.398
- Dash?

745
00:29:53.432 --> 00:29:54.965
- I think I might be in some trouble.

746
00:29:57.532 --> 00:29:59.432
- Fellas.

747
00:29:59.465 --> 00:30:00.131
Wait. wait. wait. wait. wait. wait. wait.

748
00:30:00.165 --> 00:30:00.998
I'm sorry about the confusion.

749
00:30:01.031 --> 00:30:02.131
Your money. it's being transferred.

750
00:30:02.165 --> 00:30:04.597
It's just the app. you know. it takes a few days. so--

751
00:30:07.431 --> 00:30:09.164
- Okay. where are you?

752
00:30:09.197 --> 00:30:11.631
- Closet. Dad's apartment.

753
00:30:11.664 --> 00:30:12.697
They're beating him up.

754
00:30:12.731 --> 00:30:13.997
- I can get your money.

755
00:30:14.029 --> 00:30:16.263
Just one more day. like two tops.

756
00:30:16.296 --> 00:30:18.430
Wait. wait. wait. wait. no.

757
00:30:18.463 --> 00:30:20.129
- All right. stay hidden until we get there.

758
00:30:20.163 --> 00:30:22.096
- I can't.

759
00:30:22.129 --> 00:30:24.395
They'll kill him. I have to do something.

760
00:30:24.429 --> 00:30:25.495
- No. Dash.

761
00:30:25.529 --> 00:30:27.629
Dash. no.

762
00:30:30.461 --> 00:30:32.161
- I know how you can get your money.

763
00:30:32.194 --> 00:30:33.428
- Who the hell is this?

764
00:30:33.461 --> 00:30:35.327
- It's my neighbor. He waters my plants.

765
00:30:39.427 --> 00:30:40.694
- You are such a liar.

766
00:30:40.728 --> 00:30:44.126
Although lying to protect your kid is almost noble.

767
00:30:44.160 --> 00:30:46.293
Be ashamed if I had to break all his teeth.

768
00:30:46.326 --> 00:30:47.693
stomp both his hands into soup.

769
00:30:47.727 --> 00:30:50.559
- Pass and pass.

770
00:30:50.593 --> 00:30:53.125
How about we go with my plan instead--

771
00:30:53.159 --> 00:30:55.426
rob a bunch of rich kids that go to my school?

772
00:30:55.459 --> 00:30:57.391
Who wants a Rolex?

773
00:30:59.391 --> 00:31:01.558
- You better not be lying. kid.

774
00:31:01.592 --> 00:31:03.258
Your dad is out of free passes.

775
00:31:05.591 --> 00:31:07.558
Let's go.

776
00:31:11.457 --> 00:31:13.558
- Dash would never knowingly put someone in danger.

777
00:31:13.590 --> 00:31:14.990
- So we track down whether

778
00:31:15.023 --> 00:31:16.690
any school families are out of town.

779
00:31:16.724 --> 00:31:18.256
- The Laporte premiere.

780
00:31:18.289 --> 00:31:20.423
He's a pretentious auteur filmmaker.

781
00:31:20.456 --> 00:31:21.657
His new movie launches tonight.

782
00:31:21.690 --> 00:31:23.289
Autumn Harrington is in it.

783
00:31:23.322 --> 00:31:24.955
That's the girl that Dash has a crush on.

784
00:31:24.989 --> 00:31:26.189
Her address is in the system.

785
00:31:30.589 --> 00:31:32.954
- Damn. who is this chick? - Autumn?

786
00:31:32.988 --> 00:31:34.988
She's an up-and-coming it girl.

787
00:31:35.021 --> 00:31:36.555
Her new project's getting Oscar buzz.

788
00:31:36.588 --> 00:31:40.687
- Yeah. well. let's hope she get paid in diamond bracelets.

789
00:31:40.721 --> 00:31:42.387
you know. stuff that's easy to pawn.

790
00:31:42.421 --> 00:31:45.286
Otherwise. you and dad gonna find out

791
00:31:45.319 --> 00:31:48.019
what a landfill tastes like.

792
00:31:48.052 --> 00:31:49.119
Out.

793
00:31:53.186 --> 00:31:55.019
Stay with Gus until I give you the signal.

794
00:31:55.052 --> 00:31:56.452
- All right.

795
00:31:58.185 --> 00:32:00.552
- Man. for what it's worth. your dad is the biggest

796
00:32:00.585 --> 00:32:02.384
train wreck I ever met.

797
00:32:02.418 --> 00:32:04.552
My old man. he in prison--

798
00:32:04.585 --> 00:32:06.652
trying to steal a FedEx plane with a tow truck.

799
00:32:06.685 --> 00:32:08.351
- Well. if you're the ghost of my future self.

800
00:32:08.384 --> 00:32:10.184
I might just have to Virginia Woolf it.

801
00:32:11.584 --> 00:32:13.017
- I don't know what that means.

802
00:32:13.050 --> 00:32:14.250
- She was arguably the most influential

803
00:32:14.283 --> 00:32:16.417
writer of the 20th century?

804
00:32:16.450 --> 00:32:17.683
Ended it all by walking into a river

805
00:32:17.717 --> 00:32:19.283
with rocks in her pockets.

806
00:32:22.149 --> 00:32:24.282
- Nobody likes a comedian. kid.

807
00:32:24.315 --> 00:32:26.915
- I'd argue. but the gun gives you the last word.

808
00:32:29.982 --> 00:32:33.148
- Hey. if this is a set-up. I'm killing everybody. got it?

809
00:32:33.181 --> 00:32:34.549
- Yes. sir.

810
00:32:38.681 --> 00:32:41.280
- You're not my Agedashi tofu.

811
00:32:41.313 --> 00:32:43.113
- You're not supposed to be here.

812
00:32:43.147 --> 00:32:44.080
- Well. he cut me out of the movie.

813
00:32:44.113 --> 00:32:45.347
so I wasn't on the list.

814
00:32:45.380 --> 00:32:48.213
Do you know how mortifying that--

815
00:32:48.247 --> 00:32:50.279
who the hell are you? - Hey. who else in the house?

816
00:32:50.312 --> 00:32:53.146
- Nobody. My parents are in Monaco.

817
00:32:53.179 --> 00:32:54.547
- All right. get over here.

818
00:32:54.580 --> 00:32:56.279
- I don't want to.

819
00:32:56.312 --> 00:32:58.146
- No problem. I'll just shoot you.

820
00:33:04.412 --> 00:33:06.512
Hold hands. - Why?

821
00:33:06.545 --> 00:33:09.011
- Whoa. it's even bigger on the inside.

822
00:33:09.044 --> 00:33:11.977
See. this is the kind of place I'm gonna get when I get paid.

823
00:33:12.010 --> 00:33:13.377
- Hey. man. shut up.

824
00:33:13.411 --> 00:33:15.010
Stay down here with the idiot. all right?

825
00:33:15.043 --> 00:33:16.043
Steal anything that's shiny.

826
00:33:20.042 --> 00:33:21.544
Now take me to your parents' room.

827
00:33:21.577 --> 00:33:23.009
And they better have a boatload of watches and jewelry.

828
00:33:23.042 --> 00:33:24.510
- Hey. hey! - Let's go.

829
00:33:24.543 --> 00:33:26.109
- Whoa. those whiskey bottles worth. like. 500 each.

830
00:33:26.143 --> 00:33:27.009
I'm just gonna grab a couple.

831
00:33:27.042 --> 00:33:28.543
- Show me.

832
00:33:33.675 --> 00:33:34.975
- What about this?

833
00:33:35.008 --> 00:33:35.908
- The Merlot? Really?

834
00:33:35.941 --> 00:33:36.675
No. dude. those two are worth way more.

835
00:33:47.574 --> 00:33:49.906
All right. all right.

836
00:34:22.670 --> 00:34:23.537
- Hey. where's the jewelry?

837
00:34:23.570 --> 00:34:25.136
- Closet.

838
00:34:25.169 --> 00:34:27.136
- All right. all right. Come here.

839
00:34:27.169 --> 00:34:29.002
Hey. hey. stay here.

840
00:34:39.300 --> 00:34:41.402
- I cannot believe you brought them to my house.

841
00:34:41.435 --> 00:34:42.502
- I panicked. okay?

842
00:34:42.535 --> 00:34:44.134
They were gonna kill my dad.

843
00:34:44.167 --> 00:34:46.067
And besides. you weren't supposed to be here.

844
00:34:46.100 --> 00:34:48.000
I would never knowingly put you in danger.

845
00:34:48.033 --> 00:34:49.967
- Because you have the hots for me.

846
00:34:50.000 --> 00:34:52.467
- I have romantic intentions. yeah.

847
00:34:52.501 --> 00:34:54.266
But clearly. you don't share them. so--

848
00:34:54.299 --> 00:34:57.133
It's not like you're not cute.

849
00:34:57.166 --> 00:34:58.966
You're just-- - Poor?

850
00:34:58.999 --> 00:34:59.999
- Exactly.

851
00:35:05.532 --> 00:35:06.499
What are you doing?

852
00:35:06.532 --> 00:35:08.132
- Looking for a gun.

853
00:35:08.164 --> 00:35:09.365
Oh. that's not a gun.

854
00:35:09.399 --> 00:35:10.665
- Oh. - Oh.

855
00:35:10.699 --> 00:35:12.064
Oh. your parents are freaky.

856
00:35:12.097 --> 00:35:13.399
- Hey. what the hell you doing?

857
00:35:13.432 --> 00:35:15.197
Get away from there. - Oh. sorry.

858
00:35:15.231 --> 00:35:17.997
Sorry.

859
00:35:18.030 --> 00:35:19.963
- I'm never gonna be able to look at my parents

860
00:35:19.996 --> 00:35:21.263
in the eye again.

861
00:35:21.297 --> 00:35:23.230
- Me neither.

862
00:35:23.263 --> 00:35:25.230
- Hey. Andre wouldn't really hurt my kid. right?

863
00:35:25.263 --> 00:35:27.129
This is a scare tactic?

864
00:35:27.162 --> 00:35:30.630
I mean. I know I'm not a great dad. but I try. you know?

865
00:35:30.663 --> 00:35:33.129
When it's convenient for me.

866
00:35:33.162 --> 00:35:34.396
Like. I wanna be better.

867
00:35:34.429 --> 00:35:35.529
Like. I really do.

868
00:35:35.562 --> 00:35:37.228
I think about it all the time.

869
00:35:37.262 --> 00:35:40.094
Well. not all the time.

870
00:35:40.128 --> 00:35:42.396
which is the heart of the problem. really.

871
00:35:42.429 --> 00:35:43.528
I just gotta be better.

872
00:35:43.561 --> 00:35:47.361
The kid deserves a role model. not the flaming hot mess

873
00:35:47.395 --> 00:35:49.660
I am on a daily basis.

874
00:35:49.694 --> 00:35:51.361
It feels really good to come clean about this.

875
00:35:51.395 --> 00:35:53.360
you know. it's kind of cathartic--augh!

876
00:35:53.394 --> 00:35:54.460
When the hell did you get here?

877
00:35:54.494 --> 00:35:55.527
- Where's Dash?

878
00:35:55.560 --> 00:35:56.959
- Let's go.

879
00:35:56.992 --> 00:35:58.527
- No. she's staying here.

880
00:35:58.560 --> 00:36:00.226
She hasn't seen your face. so you're in the clear.

881
00:36:00.260 --> 00:36:01.526
Just. you can do whatever you wanna me.

882
00:36:01.559 --> 00:36:02.593
Just let her go.

883
00:36:02.626 --> 00:36:04.393
- Hey. man. you got balls. kid. unlike your father.

884
00:36:04.426 --> 00:36:05.393
But she cannot stay here. all right?

885
00:36:05.426 --> 00:36:07.091
Let's go.

886
00:36:07.125 --> 00:36:07.991
- There's a gold bar in that bedside table.

887
00:36:08.024 --> 00:36:09.125
- Yeah. right.

888
00:36:09.158 --> 00:36:10.226
- I'm serious.

889
00:36:10.259 --> 00:36:12.525
But if you wanna leave it. like...

890
00:36:12.558 --> 00:36:14.124
- Stay right here.

891
00:36:14.157 --> 00:36:15.291
Don't move.

892
00:36:18.425 --> 00:36:20.524
Oh!

893
00:36:20.557 --> 00:36:22.257
- Get back.

894
00:36:22.290 --> 00:36:25.089
Drop it.

895
00:36:25.123 --> 00:36:26.656
Come on. get up.

896
00:36:28.022 --> 00:36:29.523
Hey. you two okay?

897
00:36:29.556 --> 00:36:31.590
- Physically.

898
00:36:31.623 --> 00:36:33.988
- Here. Give me these.

899
00:36:34.021 --> 00:36:35.456
Come here.

900
00:36:35.490 --> 00:36:36.523
- Ow.

901
00:36:36.556 --> 00:36:38.256
Thanks.

902
00:36:38.289 --> 00:36:40.322
And thanks for trying to save me.

903
00:36:40.355 --> 00:36:41.589
- Yeah. anytime.

904
00:36:41.622 --> 00:36:44.322
- Oh. thank God.

905
00:36:44.355 --> 00:36:47.222
Although I knew it was all gonna be all right.

906
00:36:47.255 --> 00:36:50.388
Hey. maybe we don't tell your mom about this.

907
00:36:50.421 --> 00:36:51.521
You know. we just keep it a bro thing.

908
00:36:51.554 --> 00:36:54.120
So we can-- - Stop. Just stop.

909
00:36:54.153 --> 00:36:55.653
Everything that you do. everything that you say

910
00:36:55.687 --> 00:36:59.453
is just so selfish. so toxic.

911
00:36:59.487 --> 00:37:02.253
You haven't done one fatherly thing for me in my entire life.

912
00:37:02.286 --> 00:37:03.487
All you care about is yourself.

913
00:37:03.520 --> 00:37:06.519
And I'm just sick of it.

914
00:37:06.552 --> 00:37:08.652
I'm done with you forever.

915
00:37:08.686 --> 00:37:10.252
- What?

916
00:37:18.017 --> 00:37:20.585
- So we met with all 27 defendants.

917
00:37:20.618 --> 00:37:21.851
- It's the craziest thing.

918
00:37:21.883 --> 00:37:24.450
We tried our hardest. none of them would accept a plea deal.

919
00:37:24.484 --> 00:37:25.484
- Not a one.

920
00:37:25.517 --> 00:37:26.983
- Well. I hope you've kept your weekends clear.

921
00:37:27.016 --> 00:37:28.949
because now you've got 27 trials

922
00:37:28.982 --> 00:37:29.982
you're gonna need to prepare for.

923
00:37:32.015 --> 00:37:34.116
- About that.

924
00:37:34.150 --> 00:37:35.116
I quit.

925
00:37:35.150 --> 00:37:37.216
And I'd say best of luck.

926
00:37:37.249 --> 00:37:39.383
but I hope you fail spectacularly.

927
00:37:39.416 --> 00:37:40.648
Sorry. Sean. I just can't.

928
00:37:40.682 --> 00:37:41.582
- No. no worries.

929
00:37:41.615 --> 00:37:44.081
I can't either.

930
00:37:44.115 --> 00:37:46.215
I quit too.

931
00:37:46.248 --> 00:37:47.482
Hey. what do you think of the law firm

932
00:37:47.515 --> 00:37:48.482
of Del Monte and Evers?

933
00:37:48.515 --> 00:37:49.980
- Well. you haven't worked a day in your life

934
00:37:50.013 --> 00:37:51.115
as a defense attorney.

935
00:37:51.148 --> 00:37:54.080
Evers and Del Monte.

936
00:37:54.115 --> 00:37:55.079
- Turn to the right.

937
00:37:55.114 --> 00:37:56.079
- Way ahead of you.

938
00:37:56.114 --> 00:37:57.946
Not my first rodeo.

939
00:37:57.979 --> 00:37:59.979
- Now we just need your clothes for evidence.

940
00:38:00.012 --> 00:38:03.313
and then you're free to go.

941
00:38:03.346 --> 00:38:05.246
- After everything that happened?

942
00:38:05.279 --> 00:38:07.078
- The DA may still press charges.

943
00:38:07.113 --> 00:38:10.213
but it was pretty clear you were under duress.

944
00:38:10.246 --> 00:38:12.345
- I really wanted this time to be different.

945
00:38:12.379 --> 00:38:15.445
I was gonna buy a Dash a car with a Tiger Bear on it

946
00:38:15.479 --> 00:38:17.612
to make up for lost time. you know.

947
00:38:17.644 --> 00:38:19.444
But he's right.

948
00:38:19.478 --> 00:38:21.212
I screw everything up.

949
00:38:21.244 --> 00:38:22.611
He's better off without me.

950
00:38:22.644 --> 00:38:25.378
- Probably.

951
00:38:25.411 --> 00:38:29.111
I've had some experience with bad fathers and the love

952
00:38:29.144 --> 00:38:31.243
that sons feel for them no matter how many times

953
00:38:31.276 --> 00:38:33.243
they get their hearts broken.

954
00:38:33.276 --> 00:38:34.975
And unless you're willing to change.

955
00:38:35.008 --> 00:38:38.975
and I mean really change.

956
00:38:39.008 --> 00:38:40.975
the best thing you can do for Dash

957
00:38:41.008 --> 00:38:43.941
is just leave him the hell alone.

958
00:38:52.508 --> 00:38:55.208
- What were you thinking?

959
00:38:55.241 --> 00:38:57.241
- I'm fine. Thanks for asking.

960
00:38:57.274 --> 00:38:58.374
- Do you know how close you were to becoming

961
00:38:58.407 --> 00:38:59.973
a missing person yourself?

962
00:39:00.006 --> 00:39:01.374
If she would have succeeded in killing you.

963
00:39:01.407 --> 00:39:02.607
how would I have known?

964
00:39:02.640 --> 00:39:04.474
The first thing she'd do is destroy your phone.

965
00:39:04.507 --> 00:39:06.639
So when I pulled your last known location.

966
00:39:06.673 --> 00:39:08.639
it would be your building.

967
00:39:08.673 --> 00:39:10.239
So to me and the world. you were home.

968
00:39:10.272 --> 00:39:12.339
and then you vanished.

969
00:39:12.373 --> 00:39:14.373
- I see that now.

970
00:39:14.406 --> 00:39:16.372
It's just. I figured I'd stop by and ask a few questions.

971
00:39:16.405 --> 00:39:18.138
- We have protocols for a reason.

972
00:39:20.105 --> 00:39:22.105
- Yes. sir.

973
00:39:22.138 --> 00:39:25.504
I let my best intentions obscure my judgment

974
00:39:25.537 --> 00:39:29.070
proving I still have a lot to learn about this job.

975
00:39:29.104 --> 00:39:33.237
You know. but if I can be so bold as to ask a favor...

976
00:39:37.136 --> 00:39:39.236
- You can ask.

977
00:39:39.269 --> 00:39:42.036
- I remain undaunted.

978
00:39:42.069 --> 00:39:44.103
So if a file comes across your desk

979
00:39:44.136 --> 00:39:46.635
that gives you a feeling. call me.

980
00:39:46.669 --> 00:39:51.102
I am happy to run down any lead I can for you free of charge.

981
00:39:55.267 --> 00:39:57.334
- Deal.

982
00:39:57.368 --> 00:39:59.434
And for what it's worth...

983
00:39:59.468 --> 00:40:01.368
I'm glad you're okay.

984
00:40:16.965 --> 00:40:19.498
- Your dad's gone. and your mom's on her way.

985
00:40:19.531 --> 00:40:20.531
- Cool.

986
00:40:23.331 --> 00:40:25.598
- Do you wanna talk about anything?

987
00:40:25.631 --> 00:40:27.896
- Uh. not really.

988
00:40:27.930 --> 00:40:31.330
I think I'm a little talked out for once.

989
00:40:31.364 --> 00:40:32.197
- Understood.

990
00:40:35.130 --> 00:40:38.629
You know. at the risk of sounding overly earnest.

991
00:40:38.663 --> 00:40:41.363
you're a very special young man.

992
00:40:41.396 --> 00:40:44.929
despite--or maybe even because of what

993
00:40:44.962 --> 00:40:47.162
your father's put you through.

994
00:40:47.196 --> 00:40:49.362
Now. I know you know that you're not him

995
00:40:49.395 --> 00:40:53.562
in any way. shape. or form.

996
00:40:53.595 --> 00:40:57.461
but I also know that family pain is emotional

997
00:40:57.494 --> 00:41:00.993
and not intellectual.

998
00:41:03.260 --> 00:41:05.593
I'm just trying to say.

999
00:41:05.626 --> 00:41:08.426
if you ever need a reminder of this conversation.

1000
00:41:08.460 --> 00:41:10.926
you have my number.

1001
00:41:10.959 --> 00:41:13.093
- Thanks.

1002
00:41:13.126 --> 00:41:14.892
And just to be clear. you're saying

1003
00:41:14.926 --> 00:41:16.592
I can call you every morning at the crack of dawn

1004
00:41:16.625 --> 00:41:18.058
just to tell me I'm awesome?

1005
00:41:18.092 --> 00:41:20.092
- No. - Every other morning?

1006
00:41:20.125 --> 00:41:22.359
- Twice a week. final offer.

1007
00:41:22.392 --> 00:41:24.025
- I can live with that--

1008
00:41:24.058 --> 00:41:25.958
if you can live with unlimited texts.

1009
00:41:25.991 --> 00:41:28.358
DMs. and social media shout-outs.

1010
00:41:28.391 --> 00:41:30.157
Just the calls?

1011
00:41:30.191 --> 00:41:32.358
Okay.

1012
00:41:32.391 --> 00:41:33.623
- Smart man.

1013
00:42:10.653 --> 00:42:11.853
- Damn it.

1013
00:42:12.305 --> 00:43:12.477
